To:   Sarah MurphyFrom:  SarahSubject:  Memory filesDateLine:  Winter 1986The anticipation becomes the routine.  You keep thinking about how his skin feels, the mottled blue veins under the pale cream back.  Now the Almond Cafe is a prelude, a wonderment where you can stare into clear the rose petal of wine outlined on the table cloth and tense in anticipation.Each time he tells you this is the last time.  He is busy, he says.  He no longer says he loves you.You aren't really what I want, he means.   You know this.  But your belly tenses of its own accord.  ##Higher##Lower___________________Sarah/ Moon/ Laurel___________________